27/03/2005
WASHINGTON, United States -- During a meeting with Greek Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis in Washington on Thursday (24 March), US Secretary of State Condoleeza Rice praised Greek-US bilateral co-operation as well as Greece's role in the stabilisation of the Balkans. Local press reported that talks between Rice and Molyviatis focused on Kosovo, the Cyprus problem and Greek-Turkish ties. (ANA, Kathimerini - 26/03/05)
